  "prompt": "How far is the Sun from Earth?",
  "response": "The average distance from the **Sun** to the **Earth** is approximately **93 million miles** (about **150 million kilometers**). This distance is also defined as **1 Astronomical Unit (AU)**, a standard unit of measurement used in astronomy to describe distances within our solar system.\n\nHowever, it's important to note that Earth's orbit around the Sun is not a perfect circle but slightly elliptical. As a result, the distance between the Sun and Earth varies throughout the year:\n\n- **Perihelion** (closest approach): About **91 million miles** (147 million kilometers), occurring around early January.\n- **Aphelion** (farthest distance): About **94.5 million miles** (152 million kilometers), occurring around early July.\n\nThese variations in distance contribute to seasonal changes, although the primary cause of seasons is the tilt of Earth's axis rather than the distance from the Sun.",
